            • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

              Hopefully Wenger will now drop his plans to turn Alexis into a #9. He doesn't have it in him to stay in the positions where he is needed. He constantly wants to get involved, and that is partly what makes him a top player. Twice in 2 matches, we dominated the early outings yet failed to capitalise. That gave Leicester confidence and we saw how they grew into the game. The Musa shout was a penalty. My only guess is that scouting was done on the new players prior to the start of the season and Musa was flagged up as a serial diver. I don't know myself since I've only seen him in the CL. Doesn't strike me as the type to go down when there's a chance to be had. We still need a CB partner for Koscielny (although Holding did ok in this game), a world class wide player or one with world class potential and a potent finisher to play in the 9 who can also hold the ball up and bring those around him into play. Arsene needs to get his finger out, already 5 points behind our rivals.

            • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

              @ElikaPark- Leicester dived a fair bit last year so that didn't help Musa's claim. You get tarred with the same brush when you play for a dive happy team even if you aren't that way inclined yourself. I would want a retrospective red card for dives and the rule be changed so SUFFICIENT contact needs to be made before a foul is awarded. That would be open to interpretation by referees but I'm sure they would realise the force needed to bring an athlete down would be considerable barring the instances where one or both players are running at speed, which decreases the force needed obviously. I would disagree brining a winger in would create overcrowding. We need to make the pitch big so Cazorla and Oezil have space to pass into, the best way to do that is with 2 wingers who like taking people on on the foot of the side of the pitch they are on (Alexis on the RW, not LW for example). A striker is the most immediate problem but I feel we need all 3 signings to compete for the title.

              @sampo Yes, usually refs do give those, but that doesn't make it right. What Musa did was run into Bellerin's path, then stick his legs between Bellerin's to draw out the foul. By analogy, do you want to see penalties given for unintentional and unavoidable handballs? Most people would say no. And I say no, I don't want to see penalties given for what Musa did there. Just because "99.99999999%" of people disagree doesn't mean I'm wrong.

            • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

              Koscielny, Oezil and Giroud probably wont play this game. They've had hardly any training and rushing them back could cause more injury problems. We should however, start Cazorla if he is now 100%. He changed the dynamic in midfield for us against Liverpool and there's little wonder. I would also start Xhaka along with Coquelin. Coquelin did ok against Liverpool, put in some good tackles. Xhaka gives balance in CM being left footed so I'd give him the nod over Elneny.
